# ğŸ”„ Reusing Automation in Other Projects

## ğŸ“¦ Quick Answer

**Yes!** These automation scripts can be used in:
- âœ… **Python projects** (works out of the box)
- âœ… **Node.js/JavaScript projects** (with modifications)
- âœ… **Java/Maven projects** (with modifications)
- âœ… **Any language** with package managers and build tools

The **concepts are universal** - only the commands need to change.

---

## ğŸš€ Method 1: Python Projects (Copy & Paste)

### For Another Python Project:

```bash
# 1. Copy automation files to new project
cp check_compatibility.py /path/to/new-project/
cp check_compatibility.sh /path/to/new-project/
cp setup_checks.sh /path/to/new-project/
cp .github/workflows/compatibility-check.yml /path/to/new-project/.github/workflows/

# 2. Update project-specific values
cd /path/to/new-project
vim check_compatibility.py  # Update critical_imports list
vim setup_checks.sh         # Update if needed

# 3. Run setup
./setup_checks.sh
```

### What to Customize:

**In `check_compatibility.py`:**
```python
# Line ~115: Update this list for your project
critical_imports = [
    "dash",              # â† Replace with your imports
    "plotly",            # â† 
    "pandas",            # â†
    "numpy",             # â†
    "gunicorn"           # â†
]
```

**In `.github/workflows/compatibility-check.yml`:**
```yaml
# Line ~7: Update branch names if different
on:
  push:
    branches: [ main, develop ]  # â† Your branches

# Line ~48: Update test command
- name: âœ… Verify app syntax
  run: |
    python -m py_compile app.py  # â† Your main file
```

